- **`analytics.rs`** - Email tracking and analytics functionality

- **`testing.rs`** - Testing/capture functionality (capture, list, show, clear, export)

- **`queue_work.rs`** - Work processing functionality for background job execution
- **`queue_status.rs`** - Status monitoring functionality for queue inspection
- **`queue_scheduler.rs`** - Scheduled commands and daemon functionality for cron-like jobs

### 🔐 **`auth.rs`** (761 lines → 3 modules)
- **`auth_setup.rs`** - Auth system setup and configuration
- **`auth_scaffold.rs`** - Scaffolding (user models, controllers, migrations)
- **`auth_generators.rs`** - Key generation functionality

### 🆕 **`new.rs`** (492 lines → 2 modules)
- **`new_app.rs`** - Main application creation functionality
- **`new_templates.rs`** - Template generation and file creation

### ⚙️ **`interactive_setup.rs`** (410 lines → 2 modules)
- **`interactive_wizard.rs`** - Interactive project setup wizard functionality
- **`interactive_config.rs`** - Configuration collection and generation

## Key Benefits

- ✅ **Improved maintainability**: Each module has a single, focused responsibility
- ✅ **Better code organization**: Related functionality is grouped together logically
- ✅ **Enhanced readability**: Smaller, more manageable files are easier to navigate
- ✅ **Zero breaking changes**: All existing functionality preserved with the same public API
- ✅ **Consistent patterns**: Modular structure follows the same pattern across all commands
- ✅ **Future development**: New features can be added to the appropriate module

- ✅ **CLI functionality**: All commands work exactly as before
- ✅ **Help system**: All help commands display correctly
- ✅ **Module integration**: Proper re-export structure maintains original public interface

## Technical Details

### Module Structure

```
crates/cli/src/commands/[command]/
├── mod.rs              # Module declarations and re-exports
├── [command]_[area].rs # Focused functionality modules
```

- External code using these modules requires no changes
- All CLI commands maintain their exact same behavior and help text

- **Focused modules**: Each module has a clear, single responsibility
- **Clean separation**: Related functionality is properly grouped
- **Consistent imports**: All dependencies correctly maintained across modules
- **Documentation**: Each module includes appropriate documentation
- **Error handling**: All original error handling logic preserved

![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

There's a circular dependency between the `core` and `testing` modules. `core::send` calls `testing::is_capture_enabled` and `testing::capture_email_to_filesystem`, while `testing::capture_email_to_filesystem` depends on `core::EmailSendArgs`. This makes the code harder to maintain and reason about.

To break this cycle, you could introduce a new module, for example `types.rs`, within the `email` command's directory. You can move shared data structures like `EmailSendArgs` into `types.rs`. Then both `core.rs` and `testing.rs` can depend on `types.rs` without depending on each other directly.

## 概要
観戦記録を登録するためのフォーム機能を実装しました。

## 変更内容
### 新規コンポーネント
- **GameRegistrationButton**: 観戦記録登録ボタン
  - フローティングアクションボタンスタイル
  - クリックでダイアログを開く

- **GameRegistrationDialog**: 観戦記録登録ダイアログ
  - モーダルダイアログとして実装
  - 入力フォーム（日付、対戦相手、スタジアム、スコア、結果、メモ）
  - バリデーション機能
  - 必須項目にアスタリスク表示

### 機能追加
- ESCキーでダイアログを閉じる機能
- ダイアログ外クリックで閉じる機能
- フォーム送信時の基本的なバリデーション
- レスポンシブデザイン対応

### UI/UX改善
- GameListコンポーネントにフローティングボタンを統合
- 必須項目の視覚的表示
- スムーズなダイアログ開閉アニメーション

### その他
- .gitignoreにGitHub CLI用テンプレートファイルを追加

## 関連Issue
Closes #3

## テスト内容
- [ ] 登録ボタンクリックでダイアログが開くことを確認
- [ ] 必須項目未入力時にバリデーションエラーが表示されることを確認
- [ ] ESCキー、ダイアログ外クリックで閉じることを確認
- [ ] フォーム送信（console.log出力）が正常に動作することを確認
- [ ] レスポンシブデザインが正しく動作することを確認

## 今後の課題
- APIとの連携実装
- エラーハンドリングの詳細実装
- フォーム送信後の成功メッセージ表示
- 登録データの一覧への反映

<!--
Thanks for contributing to Valkey GLIDE!

Please make sure you are aware of our contributing guidelines [available
here](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-glide/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md)

-->

Implement a framework for retrieving the protobuf ConnectionRequest message
that the PHP ValkeyGlide and ValkeyGlideCluster constructors generate.

Add tests to validate various command inputs by examining the message
deserialized into PHP protobuf classes.

Fix various bugs:
- When using multiple addresses only the first address was used.
- Reconnection strategy was not being used.
- Client AZ was not being used.
- Connection timeout was not being used.
- Disabling periodic checks did not disable it correctly.
- Made defaults for connection timeout and reconnection strategy consistent with Rust client.

Integrate tests into CI:
- Register the test class
- Install PHP dependencies through composer in CI
- Generate PHP protobuf objects in CI
- Add dependency on symfony-polyfill to resolve issues finding ctype_* functions
